        <h4>Marine Insurance</h4>
        <p>Marine Insurance is a contract that provides financial protection 
            against loss or damage to ships, cargo, and related property during
            transit by sea, air, or land. It safeguards exporters, importers, and
            vessel owners from risks like accidents, natural calamities, piracy, and 
            theft, ensuring secure and smooth global trade.</p>
        <h4>What is marine transit insurance?</h4>
        <p>Marine transit insurance, often called marine cargo insurance, 
            safeguards your goods against financial losses if they are damaged
            due to natural or man-made causes while in transit. It provides protection
            for shipments moving from the point of origin to the final destination,
            whether transported by road, rail, air, or sea.</p>
        <p>This type of insurance compensates for losses your
            cargo may face during transit from risks such as 
            fire, explosion, hijacking, accidents, collisions, 
            overturning, theft, or adverse weather conditions. 
            The coverage can be customized to suit your business needs</p>
		
